e onset of\nmass loss from the white dwarf was rapid, providing indirect evidence that the\nDES was expelled by the thermonuclear runaway event. Reprocessed X-rays from\nthe shock absorbed by the DES at early times may contribute significantly to\nthe optical/UV emission, which we speculate is responsible for the previously\nunexplained `plateaus' and secondary maxima in nova optical light curves.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Mar 2014 21:00:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
