{"id":"1403.1627","submitter":"Markus Pflaum","authors":"Bryce Chriestenson and Markus J. Pflaum","title":"Whitney functions determine the real homotopy type of a semi-analytic\n  set","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.AT math.CV","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this paper, we investigate the Whitney--de Rham complex\n$\\Omega^\\bullet_\\text{W} (X)$ associated to a semi-analytic subset $X$ of an\nanalytic manifold $M$. This complex is a commutative differential graded\nalgebra, that is defined to be the quotient of the de Rham complex of smooth\ndifferential forms on $M$ by the differential graded ideal generated by all\nsmooth functions which are flat on $X$. We use Hironaka's desingularization\ntheorem to prove a Poincar\\'e Lemma for $\\Omega^\\bullet_\\text{W} (X)$ holds\ntrue, which entails that its cohomology is isomorphic to the real cohomology of\n$X$. Furthermore, we show that this isomorphism is induced by a\nquasi-isomorphism of differential graded algebras. Thus it preserves the\nproduct structure, and is therefore an isomorphism of commutative differential\ngraded algebras. As a consequence we show, when $X$ is simply connected, that\nthe Whitney--de Rham complex determines the real homotopy type of $X$. This\nallows one further to conclude that the Hochschild homology of the differential\ngraded algebra $\\Omega^\\bullet_\\text{W} (X)$ is isomorphic to the cohomology of\nthe free loop space $\\mathcal{L} X$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Mar 2014 00:49:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-03-10"}
